"{\"title\": \"FINANCIAL STATEMENT ANALYSIS AND VALUATION\", \"level\": \"504\", \"abbreviation\": \"FIN\", \"description\": \"This course develops expertise in financial decision-making by focusing on financial accounting information.  The course presents a comprehensive framework for financial statement analysis and valuation.  Through hands-on, practical application of various tools for financial analysis (e.g., ratio analysis & financial modeling using Excel and other resources) students will develop the expertise needed to use a firms' financial statements to draw an understanding of its performance and to provide a basis for making reasonable valuation estimates. Students will learn to apply analytical techniques to develop forecasted financial statements and use the information to value a firm\\u2019s equity. The course will utilize team assignments, cases, simulations, and other applied exercises.  (Prerequisites: ACC 500, ACC 502, & FIN 503)\", \"req\": [], \"cat1Status\": true, \"startYear\": -1}"